URL | www.waterpolo.hu | waterpolo.hu }}\n}}\nThe '''Hungary women's national water polo team''' represents [[Hungary]] in international [[women]]'s [[water polo]] competitions and friendly matches. The team is one of the leading teams in [[Europe]] since the early 1990s, claiming the world title at the [[1994 World Aquatics Championships]] in [[Rome, Italy]].\n\n==Results==\n===Olympic Games===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n!Year<ref name=\"HistoFINA PDF\">{{cite web|title=HistoFINA \u2013 Water polo medalists and statistics \u2013 Download |url=https://www.fina.org/sites/default/files/histofina_wp_2018_final_0.pdf |website=fina.org |publisher=[[FINA]] |date=September 2017 |format=PDF |pages=54, 55, 64, 74 |access-date=30 March 2020 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190528143003/https://www.fina.org/sites/default/files/histofina_wp_2018_final_0.pdf |archive-date=28 May 2019 }}</ref>\n!width=\"100\"|Position\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Greece}} [[Water polo at the 2004 Summer Olympics|2004]] || 6th place\n|- style=\"background:#9ACDFF;\"\n|{{flagicon|China}} [[Water polo at the 2008 Summer Olympics|2008]] || [[Water polo at the 2008 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's tournament|4th place]]\n|- style=\"background:#9ACDFF;\"\n|{{flagicon|Great Britain}} [[Water polo at the 2012 Summer Olympics|2012]] || [[Water polo at the 2012 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's tournament|4th place]]\n|- style=\"background:#9ACDFF;\"\n|{{flagicon|Brazil}} [[Water polo at the 2016 Summer Olympics|2016]] || [[Water polo at the 2016 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's tournament|4th place]]\n|}\n\n===World Championship===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n!Year<ref name=\"HistoFINA PDF\"/>\n!width=\"100\"|Position\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Spain}} [[1986 FINA Women's World Water Polo Championship|1986]] || 5th place\n|- style=\"background:#9ACDFF;\"\n|{{flagicon|Australia}} [[1991 FINA Women's World Water Polo Championship|1991]] || 4th pla