-treasures-of-white-house-517123.html |title=British warship sunk during war with US may hold lost treasures of White House |first=David |last= Usborne |date= November 27, 2005|work=The Independent |accessdate=January 28, 2011 |location=London}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"2ZhT4\">{{cite journal|last=Young | first= G.F.W | title= HMS ''Fantome'' and the British Raid on Washington August 1814| journal= Royal Nova Scotia Historical Society Journal| volume=10 |pages= 132\u2013145}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"KQzqy\">Haas, Irvin. ''Historic Homes of the American Presidents.'' New York: Dover Publishing, 1991, p. 30.</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"tbe3z\">{{cite book |title=The Domestic Architecture of Benjamin Henry Latrobe |publisher=The Johns Hopkins University Press |author=Michael W. Fazio and Patrick A. Snadon |year=2006 |pages=368\u2013370}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"wSPdx\">{{cite web|url=http://www.iht.com/articles/2006/09/15/opinion/edjohnson.php |title=A chateau fit for a president |accessdate=November 2, 2007 |work=International Herald Tribune |date=September 15, 2006 |last=Johnson |first=Michael |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070314011250/http://www.iht.com/articles/2006/09/15/opinion/edjohnson.php |archivedate=March 14, 2007}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"MqIIY\">{{cite news | url = http://cuatower.com/2019/10/catholic-university-could-have-been-the-white-house/ | title = Catholic University Could Have Been The White House | date = October 17, 2019 | accessdate = October 18, 2019 | newspaper = The Tower | first = Claire | last = Prudhomme}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"bFjvZ\">{{cite web|title=The Grand Illumination: Sunset of the Gaslight Age, 1891|url=http://www.whitehousehistory.org/whha_exhibits/waddell_white-house-past/tiffany-glass-painting.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110507020213/http://www.whitehousehistory.org/whha_exhibits/waddell_white-house-past/tiffany-glass-painting.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=May 7, 2011|publisher=The White House His